{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/diagnosis/confirmed-deficiency/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"7c242ba4-b4a4-5869-ba3c-eecc605d06cd","slug":"confirmed-deficiency","fullItemName":"Confirmed deficiency","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field e7072e34-7986-4621-8d92-a8a400a6a1bc --><h2>How should I manage people with confirmed vitamin B12 or folate deficiency?</h2><!-- end field e7072e34-7986-4621-8d92-a8a400a6a1bc -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2691d999-74cf-4ca0-8037-a8a400a69d78 --><!-- begin field 0f849e19-f63e-4700-848e-a8a400a6a1bc --><ul><li>Determine whether there is an underlying <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/background-information/causes/\">cause</a> for the vitamin B12 or folate deficiency — this may require specialist referral.<ul><li>If folate levels are low, assess dietary folic acid intake, and if history suggests malabsorption, check for coeliac disease by testing for antiendomysial or antitransglutaminase antibodies (depending on the local laboratory).<ul><li>The main cause of folate malabsorption is gluten-induced enteropathy. </li></ul></li><li>If cobalamin levels are low, check for serum anti-intrinsic factor antibodies.<ul><li>Also test people with strong clinical features of B12 deficiency, such as megaloblastic anaemia or subacute combined degeneration of the cord, despite a normal cobalamin level.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>Determine whether the person has experienced <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/background-information/complications/\">complications</a> of anaemia, vitamin B12 or folate deficiency.</li><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/management/management/#referral\">Refer</a> or <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/management/management/#treatment-for-folate-deficiency\">treat</a> the person where appropriate depending on the suspected cause.</li></ul><!-- end field 0f849e19-f63e-4700-848e-a8a400a6a1bc --><!-- end item 2691d999-74cf-4ca0-8037-a8a400a69d78 -->","topic":{"id":"b52ae1d2-5f6b-5c89-b542-7a9a47d77178","topicId":"cbd29368-ea95-42b6-9182-2ca865ba6f9b","topicName":"Anaemia - B12 and folate deficiency","slug":"anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2020","chapters":[{"id":"a9aeca23-e08f-58a5-9fbd-6e935b8641c4","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"2b2ba5cd-a380-5df0-8a8e-0ca42dd8fb26","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e9db4e81-3b25-5d5e-bd5c-5780aabc140d","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"e8e43295-58a5-5c7a-8cb7-d698db0a9255","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"0a685e3c-089e-5a70-aafb-92e8819b4fbe","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"ddbe6709-fe36-5dc4-93d6-5c099f6efdbb","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"7acbd2a3-7a7f-52ca-bef1-2d42a0abb1b0","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"089b0d31-4b83-5a2d-b361-a2ec31c8de08","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"0fcb78e6-89c2-5864-93df-be896d476dca","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"d705c812-e7af-5196-94f0-350ba9a76e13","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"8d0b2c45-7b5a-5f7b-b4c1-eda2e197a05a","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"80b26201-53cf-5f4e-8b13-7a4b86c68b7b","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"03f7f696-dfb6-5cd5-b0c6-4abd560850a6","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"d1cf8723-0abb-5b4e-8a8f-d2c925e3df1d","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"c38d10d4-bd56-5953-a432-ee8372e84677","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"f2865caa-3d82-5f2f-9596-c9b11520fe59","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"22aa28f7-8f78-5523-a73d-ede787c2d1ab","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"e53704e0-f6e9-50ac-8ad3-bc56f54beb1d","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"d8a58de8-7db8-5b58-a0c7-4d6ab8b89aed","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"e8a672a3-78d3-5053-a329-2b1ae0b0cc6c","slug":"signs-symptoms","fullItemName":"Signs and symptoms"},{"id":"f6e910a1-da9d-5884-a9d6-995ac83f8ac7","slug":"investigations","fullItemName":"Investigations"},{"id":"48e2fad1-dda9-5ed4-b44e-99f31796f240","slug":"interpreting-investigation-results","fullItemName":"Interpreting investigation results"},{"id":"7c242ba4-b4a4-5869-ba3c-eecc605d06cd","slug":"confirmed-deficiency","fullItemName":"Confirmed deficiency"},{"id":"d3ccb7ec-b4da-5893-bd60-db328eac25e9","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"b6a6002f-8548-52a4-81ca-13d422af2223","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"0b4cd630-88ee-5438-806f-76bb07c74f37","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"623f6c15-7fbb-56ac-b388-61051f7042e6","fullItemName":"Prescribing information","slug":"prescribing-information","subChapters":[{"id":"5e69cf84-76bf-5e84-8682-f1afe972f2a0","slug":"cyanocobalamin","fullItemName":"Cyanocobalamin"},{"id":"71dc3c90-6de3-52c1-bfad-ec80d86197c7","slug":"folic-acid","fullItemName":"Folic acid"},{"id":"0cb22b73-fd95-5b5f-8fb6-0a30304502f1","slug":"hydroxocobalamin","fullItemName":"Hydroxocobalamin"}]},{"id":"9de372f3-434d-53c4-9d5b-691bce9e825c","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"286b176b-2cb4-5134-8a4e-9ec092ea453d","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"2103df03-f0e3-50b6-a72d-5663689a46dd","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"51c0528f-a858-5b34-92d3-37cd634cd985","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"9247059c-e354-50a4-a37d-5f05262d9664","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"ca415a22-e1dc-5ff8-866c-2a7620ca866d","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"ab29e744-4028-5d68-ace0-9d5ba3e27c47","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"03e63b3a-540a-55bd-ab53-ff3870ad4f15","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"e53704e0-f6e9-50ac-8ad3-bc56f54beb1d","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"ca7083a0-56da-53dc-8fc0-9506b5255339","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-baf","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 28bc7578-253b-485d-b057-a8a400ae0976 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 28bc7578-253b-485d-b057-a8a400ae0976 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item baff3908-86de-4716-97f2-a8a400ae08cd --><!-- begin field b360d221-2dbd-4e77-884c-a8a400ae0976 --><p>These recommendations are based on expert opinion in the British Journal of Haematology <em>Guidelines for the diagnosis and treatment of cobalamin and folate disorders </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/references/\">Devalia et al, 2014</a>], and expert opinion in review articles in medical textbooks <em>Macrocytic anaemias </em>in the <em>ABC of Clinical Haematology </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/references/\">Hoffbrand and Provan, 2007</a>] and <em>Megaloblastic anaemia and miscellaneous deficiency anaemias</em> in <em>Oxford textbook of medicine</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/references/\">Hoffbrand, 2014</a>].</p><h4>Checking for anti-intrinsic factor antibodies</h4><ul><li>Anti-intrinsic factor antibody is extremely specific for pernicious anaemia, with a high positive predictive value of 95%, but a low sensitivity of 40–60%. If anti-intrinsic factor antibody is present, pernicious anaemia is very likely, but its absence does not rule out a diagnosis of pernicious anaemia [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/anaemia-b12-folate-deficiency/references/\">Devalia et al, 2014</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field b360d221-2dbd-4e77-884c-a8a400ae0976 --><!-- end item baff3908-86de-4716-97f2-a8a400ae08cd -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}